Family 
<taxonomicName box="[246,409,296,322]" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mesoveliidae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,366,499]" box="[151,531,366,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant &amp; Rey" authorityName="Mulsant &amp; Rey" box="[151,531,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" genus="Mesovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[151,353,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Mesovelia furcata</emphasis>
Mulsant &amp; Rey
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,366,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
Usually inhabits ponds overgrown with water lilies, often forming aggregations on floating leaves of aquatic vegetation or on the surface of standing waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[711,912,438,463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Aquatic Heteroptera (Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauna of Russia and neighboring regions. Russian Academies of Sciences of the Far East, Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, pp. 297. [Kaнюkova, I. V. (2006) Vodныi poлuziсtkokрылыi нaсikoмыi фauны Рoссii i сopрidiльныk сtрaн]." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kanyukova 
<number box="[851,912,438,463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); zoophage; multivoltine; overwinter as eggs. West Palearctic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,546,679]" box="[151,478,546,571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName authority="Horvath" authorityName="Horvath" box="[151,478,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" genus="Mesovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermalis">
<emphasis box="[151,379,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Mesovelia thermalis</emphasis>
Horvath
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,546,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
In permanent ponds and lakes, preferring those with surfaces completely overgrown with duckweed in the summer; also occurs in the quiet backwaters of lowland rivers with slow currents and warm water, associated with aquatic vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[370,569,654,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Aquatic Heteroptera (Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauna of Russia and neighboring regions. Russian Academies of Sciences of the Far East, Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, pp. 297. [Kaнюkova, I. V. (2006) Vodныi poлuziсtkokрылыi нaсikoмыi фauны Рoссii i сopрidiльныk сtрaн]." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kanyukova 
<number box="[508,569,654,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); zoophage; multivoltine; overwinters in the egg stage. Mid-Tethys.
</paragraph>
